natively, the coupling between the\nin-streaming gas and the disc may weaken in time, reflecting an evolving nature\nof the accretion. If, instead, that coupling is weak at all times, the likely\nenergy source for self-regulated stirring up of the turbulence is the inflow\nwithin the disc down the potential gradient (studied in a companion paper).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 5 Mar 2012 03:46:18 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 4 Jul 2012 22:19:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-04"}
